    <text id="F8506T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McPherson offers his suggestions to an unknown recipient for committee members
                    from Franklin County and Adams County.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
             

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1857-07-01">July 1. 57.</date>
                        <name type="place">
                            <abbr expan="Gettysburg">Gettybg</abbr>
                        </name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Dear">D</abbr> Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p><abbr expan="Your">Yr.</abbr> Circular of the 17<hi rend="super">th</hi> reached
                    me some days ago. I immediately wrote to <unclear>Chambersburg</unclear> for the
                    Franklin <abbr expan="Committee">Com<hi rend="super">te</hi></abbr>. Returning
                    home yesterday evening, I found a reply awaiting me. I presume you wished me to
                    give <abbr expan="committees">comtes</abbr> only for those Counties which
                    comprised our Senatorial district, when the <abbr expan="National">Natl</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Committee">Comte.</abbr> was appointed. The Bedford man will
                        <unclear>supply</unclear> you with the Fulton <abbr expan="subcommittee"
                        >sub-comte</abbr>.</p>

                <p>I suggest the names of the following persons:</p>

                <p><hi rend="underline">Franklin</hi> -- A.N. Rankin, Chambersburg<lb/><abbr
                        expan="George">Geo.</abbr> W. Ziegler, Greencastle<lb/><abbr
                        expan="Honorable">Hon.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Thomas">Thos.</abbr> Dumroy, Roxbury</p>

                <p>Adams -- David A. Buehler -- Gettysburg<lb/>Dr. J. L. Hill<lb/>Dr. Charles Horner</p>

                <p>We have thought it best for the sake of efficiency to have the <abbr
                        expan="committee">comte.</abbr> in town. In Chambersburg they preferred the
                    other plan.--</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours truly</salute>
                    <signed><abbr expan="Edward">Edwd</abbr> McPherson</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
